1
00:00:07,473 --> 00:00:09,510
Narrator: WITH THE HELP
OF CAESAR'S BANDANA,

2
00:00:09,576 --> 00:00:12,946
JOJO BARELY MANAGED
TO DEFEAT WAMUU.

3
00:00:16,683 --> 00:00:19,953
THEN IT WAS KARS'S TURN
TO FACE LISA LISA

4
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,321
IN THEIR ONE‐ON‐ONE COMBAT.

5
00:00:21,354 --> 00:00:23,524
♪

6
00:00:23,624 --> 00:00:27,293
SUDDENLY VON STROHEIM SHOWED UP
TO BATTLE THE VAMPIRES,

7
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,996
ALONG WITH SPEEDWAGON
AND SMOKEY.

8
00:00:31,765 --> 00:00:37,370
IN A COWARDLY TURN, KARS USED
A DOUBLE TO DECEIVE LISA LISA.

9
00:00:37,470 --> 00:00:40,140
THEN HE LITERALLY
STABBED HER IN THE BACK

10
00:00:40,206 --> 00:00:43,343
TO USE AS A PAWN AGAINST JOJO.

11
00:00:43,376 --> 00:00:44,845
JOJO AND LISA LISA

12
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:47,013
ARE IN THE GREATEST PERIL
OF THEIR LIVES.

13
00:00:48,114 --> 00:00:49,883
( JoJo yells )

14
00:00:49,983 --> 00:00:51,785
KARS, YOU BASTARD!

15
00:00:51,852 --> 00:00:55,121
THERE'S A PLACE
WAITING FOR YOU IN HELL!

16
00:00:55,188 --> 00:00:56,557
Smokey: JOJO DOESN'T KNOW.

17
00:00:56,623 --> 00:00:59,726
HE DOESN'T KNOW THE WOMAN
HE'S TRYING TO SAVE

18
00:00:59,826 --> 00:01:01,201
IS HIS MOTHER.

19
00:01:01,234 --> 00:01:04,137
( men's chorus singing )

20
00:01:12,212 --> 00:01:13,914
( JoJo grunts )

21
00:01:16,216 --> 00:01:19,152
Kars: YOU DON'T WANT
TO LET GO OF THAT, JOJO.

22
00:01:19,219 --> 00:01:22,255
IT'S A FOREST
OF CRYSTAL SPIKES DOWN THERE.

23
00:01:22,322 --> 00:01:24,057
SHE WOULD DIE HORRIBLY.

24
00:01:25,158 --> 00:01:26,092
JoJo: KARS!

25
00:01:26,159 --> 00:01:27,928
YOU HAVE LIVED FOR FAR TOO LONG.

26
00:01:28,028 --> 00:01:29,229
YOUR SOUL'S DECAYED.

27
00:01:29,262 --> 00:01:32,599
IT'S LIKE A PUMPKIN LEFT TO ROT
OUT IN A DEAD FIELD.

28
00:01:32,666 --> 00:01:33,700
EVEN FLIES AVOID IT.

29
00:01:33,767 --> 00:01:35,569
Kars: YES, GRUMBLE AT ME.

30
00:01:35,602 --> 00:01:38,939
SHOUT YOUR LUNGS OUT.
HEAVE YOUR INSULTS AT ME,

31
00:01:39,039 --> 00:01:41,742
FOR AS LONG AS YOU'RE
HOLDING ON TO THAT ROPE,

32
00:01:41,775 --> 00:01:44,177
MY FRIEND,
THAT'S ABOUT ALL YOU CAN DO.

33
00:01:44,244 --> 00:01:46,947
( JoJo growls )

34
00:01:47,047 --> 00:01:48,949
( chorus continues )

35
00:01:52,185 --> 00:01:54,120
♪

36
00:01:58,592 --> 00:02:00,734
( singing in Japanese )

37
00:03:25,391 --> 00:03:27,561
♪

38
00:03:41,675 --> 00:03:43,810
( JoJo grunting )

39
00:03:47,413 --> 00:03:49,315
‐ ( JoJo groans )
‐ ( both gasp )

40
00:03:55,421 --> 00:03:57,357
( JoJo panting )

41
00:03:59,726 --> 00:04:01,735
Speedwagon: JOJO! LISA LISA!

42
00:04:01,768 --> 00:04:04,571
Smokey: HE CAN'T FOLLOW
WHAT'S REALLY GOING ON.

43
00:04:04,605 --> 00:04:07,741
HE DOESN'T REALIZE
THAT'S HIS MOTHER HE'S HOLDING.

44
00:04:07,774 --> 00:04:11,011
MR. SPEEDWAGON,
WE NEED TO TELL JOJO.

45
00:04:11,878 --> 00:04:12,779
Speedwagon: NOT YET.

46
00:04:12,879 --> 00:04:14,047
Smokey: BUT WHY NOT?!

47
00:04:14,114 --> 00:04:16,216
Speedwagon: IT'S NOT
THE PROPER TIME.

48
00:04:16,282 --> 00:04:17,417
VON STROHEIM!

49
00:04:17,450 --> 00:04:20,286
HAVE YOU FINISHED DISPOSING
OF THOSE VAMPIRES YET?!

50
00:04:20,353 --> 00:04:21,588
WE MUST HELP JOJO.

51
00:04:21,622 --> 00:04:23,724
‐ Von Stroheim: JA, RIGHT.
‐ ( vampires yell )

52
00:04:23,790 --> 00:04:25,391
Von Stroheim: YOU THINK
I JUST HAVE TO WAVE

53
00:04:25,458 --> 00:04:29,262
MY MAGIC FLASHLIGHT
UND THEN IT'S ALL DONE?!

54
00:04:29,295 --> 00:04:31,932
( vampires screaming )

55
00:04:33,266 --> 00:04:36,603
Von Stroheim: OUT OF SIGHT
UND OUT OF MIND!

56
00:04:36,636 --> 00:04:37,804
( growling )

57
00:04:37,871 --> 00:04:39,906
( vampires growling )

58
00:04:39,973 --> 00:04:42,943
Speedwagon: VON STROHEIM HAS
GOT HIS HANDS FULL RIGHT NOW.

59
00:04:44,077 --> 00:04:45,946
Smokey: JOJO.

60
00:04:48,882 --> 00:04:50,283
Kars: CAREFUL NOW.

61
00:04:50,316 --> 00:04:53,153
THAT ROPE LOOKS LIKE
IT'S STARTING TO SLIP A LITTLE.

62
00:04:54,220 --> 00:04:54,955
( JoJo grunts )

63
00:04:54,988 --> 00:04:57,157
‐ ( growls )
‐ Kars: HMM?

64
00:04:57,257 --> 00:04:58,759
( JoJo yells )

65
00:05:00,326 --> 00:05:01,968
Kars: AS LONG
AS YOU'RE HOLDING ON

66
00:05:02,002 --> 00:05:03,904
SO TIGHTLY TO THAT ROPE,

67
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:06,406
YOUR CLUMSY FEET
HAVE LIMITED REACH.

68
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:08,108
‐ ( yells )
‐ ( JoJo screaming )

69
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:12,846
Speedwagon: OH, NO.
HIS KICK DID MAKE IT TO KARS,

70
00:05:12,913 --> 00:05:14,915
BUT THERE WAS NO HAMON.

71
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:17,283
( Smokey gasps )
WE'RE IN REAL TROUBLE.

72
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:18,418
Kars: YOU POOR BOY,

73
00:05:18,484 --> 00:05:21,154
IT LOOKS LIKE YOU'RE
RUNNING OUT OF HAMON.

74
00:05:21,187 --> 00:05:23,990
BUT IT IS POSSIBLE
YOU MIGHT HAVE ENOUGH LEFT

75
00:05:24,024 --> 00:05:26,527
TO MAKE
ONE LAST‐DITCH ATTACK ON ME.

76
00:05:26,627 --> 00:05:28,328
( JoJo growls )

77
00:05:28,361 --> 00:05:30,196
Kars: I'LL WALK UP THERE,

78
00:05:30,296 --> 00:05:33,133
AND THEN I'M GOING
TO TAKE YOUR LIFE AS EASILY

79
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:36,937
AS IF I WERE PLUCKING A LITTLE
FLOWER ALONG A GARDEN PATHWAY.

80
00:05:39,472 --> 00:05:40,373
( JoJo spits )

81
00:05:40,473 --> 00:05:42,008
‐ KARS.
‐ Kars: MMM?

82
00:05:42,042 --> 00:05:44,945
JoJo: MAYBE THERE
IS ENOUGH LEFT IN ME,

83
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:47,948
ENOUGH HAMON
FOR ONE LAST DESPERATE ATTACK.

84
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:50,383
TO BE HONEST, EVEN I DON'T KNOW.

85
00:05:50,483 --> 00:05:51,985
Kars: HMM?

86
00:05:52,052 --> 00:05:55,455
JoJo: BUT EITHER WAY,
I'VE DEVISED A CUNNING PLAN.

87
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:58,191
I GUARANTEE IT'S SOMETHING
TO MAKE YOU CHOKE.

88
00:05:58,224 --> 00:06:01,502
HOW BADLY DO YOU
WANT TO KNOW WHAT IT IS?

89
00:06:01,568 --> 00:06:03,069
'CAUSE I'M NOT TELLING!

90
00:06:03,136 --> 00:06:04,505
Kars: HEY.

91
00:06:04,571 --> 00:06:07,674
I CAN SEE THAT YOU'VE STOPPED
TYING THOSE ROPES TOGETHER NOW.

92
00:06:07,741 --> 00:06:09,042
HMM?

93
00:06:09,075 --> 00:06:10,644
JoJo: YOU SEE THIS MATCH?

94
00:06:10,711 --> 00:06:13,680
WHAT DO YOU THINK I'M GOING
TO BE DOING WITH THIS FIRE?

95
00:06:13,747 --> 00:06:15,148
Kars: HUMPH.

96
00:06:16,850 --> 00:06:19,319
Smokey: HUH?
WHAT ON EARTH IS JOJO THINKING?

97
00:06:19,385 --> 00:06:22,322
HE SET HIS SCARF ON FIRE.

98
00:06:22,388 --> 00:06:25,926
JoJo: BEFORE THIS FLAME
HAS A CHANCE TO BURN ME,

99
00:06:26,026 --> 00:06:28,829
I'M GOING TO FIND A WAY
TO USE WHATEVER I CAN

100
00:06:28,895 --> 00:06:30,564
TO SEND YOU STRAIGHT TO HELL.

101
00:06:30,597 --> 00:06:32,599
THE SCARF IS A GAMBLE,

102
00:06:32,699 --> 00:06:34,334
SOMETHING TO MOTIVATE ME,

103
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:37,437
A LITTLE PAIN
TO HELP ME FIND A WAY.

104
00:06:37,504 --> 00:06:40,440
Kars: JOJO, COME ON NOW.

105
00:06:40,507 --> 00:06:41,742
YOU CAN'T FOOL ME.

106
00:06:41,775 --> 00:06:45,746
THAT'S JUST
AN ACT OF DESPERATION!

107
00:06:45,779 --> 00:06:48,782
♪

108
00:06:51,451 --> 00:06:52,886
DON'T TOY WITH ME.

109
00:06:52,953 --> 00:06:54,788
YOU'RE JUST DODGING AROUND

110
00:06:54,888 --> 00:06:57,691
FOR A CHANCE
TO CATCH YOUR BREATH.

111
00:06:57,758 --> 00:06:59,192
IT'S NO MATTER.

112
00:06:59,259 --> 00:07:02,536
I'M TAKING YOUR LIFE
AT THE MOMENT OF MY CHOICE,

113
00:07:02,603 --> 00:07:05,038
I'M TIRED OF DEALING
WITH YOUR SILLY ANTICS.

114
00:07:05,105 --> 00:07:07,541
JoJo: OH, COME ON.
I NEED TO BREATHE.

115
00:07:07,608 --> 00:07:09,475
SO WHAT IF I
LOOK SILLY DOING IT?

116
00:07:11,745 --> 00:07:13,079
JOJO, LOOK.

117
00:07:13,146 --> 00:07:15,549
CLEARLY I CAN SEVER
LISA LISA'S ROPE

118
00:07:15,616 --> 00:07:17,618
WITH JUST A FLICK OF MY WRIST,

119
00:07:17,651 --> 00:07:21,321
AND IF YOU DODGE ME AGAIN,
THAT IS EXACTLY WHAT I WILL DO.

120
00:07:21,387 --> 00:07:22,923
( JoJo groans )

121
00:07:22,989 --> 00:07:24,625
Kars: WHAT DO YOU THINK?

122
00:07:24,658 --> 00:07:27,093
SHOULD I PRESS
JUST A LITTLE HARDER?

123
00:07:27,961 --> 00:07:28,995
( chuckles )

124
00:07:29,095 --> 00:07:31,832
IT'S SO EASY.

125
00:07:31,898 --> 00:07:34,467
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

126
00:07:34,501 --> 00:07:35,736
JoJo: DON'T DO IT!

127
00:07:35,802 --> 00:07:37,470
Kars: YOU RAN AWAY BEFORE.

128
00:07:37,504 --> 00:07:40,240
NOW COME TOWARD ME SLOWLY.

129
00:07:40,306 --> 00:07:43,143
HEH. OR YOU COULD
STAY WHERE YOU ARE

130
00:07:43,176 --> 00:07:45,846
AND WATCH AS I
CUT THROUGH THE LINE.

131
00:07:45,946 --> 00:07:47,848
‐ ( JoJo growls )
‐ Speedwagon: THE COWARD.

132
00:07:47,948 --> 00:07:49,449
Kars: SO, WHAT THEN?

133
00:07:49,516 --> 00:07:51,952
IS YOUR LIFE MORE PRECIOUS

134
00:07:52,018 --> 00:07:55,455
THAN THAT OF THE WOMAN
DANGLING DOWN THERE?

135
00:07:55,522 --> 00:07:57,357
( JoJo growls )

136
00:07:57,423 --> 00:07:58,358
HAH!

137
00:07:59,259 --> 00:08:02,503
( yells ) HERE'S MY CHOICE!

138
00:08:02,536 --> 00:08:05,038
Kars: I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING,

139
00:08:05,138 --> 00:08:06,640
BUT WHEN I CUT THIS LINE,

140
00:08:06,707 --> 00:08:09,810
YOU WILL BOTH BE IMPALED
ON THE CRYSTAL SPIKES BELOW.

141
00:08:09,876 --> 00:08:11,377
YOU FOOL!

142
00:08:12,546 --> 00:08:13,479
Smokey: JOJO!

143
00:08:13,547 --> 00:08:14,480
Speedwagon: LISA LISA!

144
00:08:14,548 --> 00:08:16,550
Kars: HEH. IDIOT.

145
00:08:16,650 --> 00:08:18,051
TWO BIRDS WITH ONE CUT.

146
00:08:18,118 --> 00:08:20,020
‐ ( JoJo grunts )
‐ Kars: HUH?

147
00:08:20,053 --> 00:08:22,388
WHAT?! BUT HE‐‐

148
00:08:22,455 --> 00:08:26,126
THIS ROPE,
IT'S CONNECTED TO JOJO.

149
00:08:26,993 --> 00:08:28,394
( both gasp )

150
00:08:28,461 --> 00:08:30,964
Kars: WHEN DID HE
MAKE THIS HAPPEN?

151
00:08:31,031 --> 00:08:33,567
HE DIDN'T HAVE ENOUGH TIME TO‐‐

152
00:08:33,667 --> 00:08:36,503
OH. WHEN HE FIRST KICKED AT ME,

153
00:08:36,570 --> 00:08:40,406
HE ALLOWED HIMSELF TO BE CUT
ALONG WITH THE ROPE.

154
00:08:40,473 --> 00:08:43,076
AND THEN WHEN HE IGNITED
THAT DAMNED MATCH,

155
00:08:43,143 --> 00:08:46,713
HE SECRETLY TIED HIS LEG
TO THE ROPE ON LISA LISA.

156
00:08:46,747 --> 00:08:48,248
I SEE IT NOW.

157
00:08:48,314 --> 00:08:51,417
HE NEEDED
SOME KIND OF DISTRACTION.

158
00:08:51,484 --> 00:08:54,020
THAT'S WHEN HE SET
HIS SCARF ON FIRE.

159
00:08:54,087 --> 00:08:55,488
( no audible dialogue )

160
00:08:55,556 --> 00:08:57,858
AND THEN TO TIE
THE LINES TOGETHER,

161
00:08:57,924 --> 00:09:00,734
HE MANEUVERED ME
INTO DOING HIS WORK FOR HIM

162
00:09:00,767 --> 00:09:02,603
BY CUTTING LISA LISA'S ROPE.

163
00:09:06,106 --> 00:09:08,441
THAT MANIPULATING CHEAT.

164
00:09:08,509 --> 00:09:12,112
JoJo: NOW YOU'RE THE ONE
SAVING BOTH ME AND LISA LISA.

165
00:09:14,180 --> 00:09:16,216
Kars: YOU DECEIVED ME, JOJO!

166
00:09:16,282 --> 00:09:19,753
JoJo: HOW ODD THAT I SHOULD HEAR
YOU COMPLAINING ABOUT TRICKERY.

167
00:09:19,786 --> 00:09:21,522
YOU ENJOY DECEIVING OTHERS,

168
00:09:21,588 --> 00:09:24,257
BUT NOW THE SHOE'S
ON THE OTHER FOOT.

169
00:09:24,290 --> 00:09:27,460
YOU MAY HAVE LIVED
FOR OVER 10,000 YEARS,

170
00:09:27,528 --> 00:09:30,130
BUT IF YOU'RE GOING UP
AGAINST MY SKILLS,

171
00:09:30,230 --> 00:09:32,465
YOU NEED ANOTHER DECADE!

172
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:34,467
YOU'RE THROUGH!

173
00:09:34,535 --> 00:09:35,636
( Kars screams )

174
00:09:35,702 --> 00:09:37,103
( JoJo yells )

175
00:09:37,137 --> 00:09:44,978
HAMON OVERDRIVE!

176
00:09:47,614 --> 00:09:49,616
( panting )

177
00:09:49,650 --> 00:09:51,084
DID IT WORK?

178
00:09:51,151 --> 00:09:54,120
THAT WAS THE LAST OF MY HAMON.

179
00:09:54,154 --> 00:09:56,089
I'M BURNED OUT.

180
00:09:56,156 --> 00:09:59,492
I DON'T HAVE
AN OUNCE OF STRENGTH LEFT.

181
00:10:00,767 --> 00:10:02,703
( Kars shuddering )

182
00:10:03,937 --> 00:10:05,906
( screams )

183
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:08,041
JoJo: YES. IT WAS ENOUGH.

184
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:09,042
Speedwagon: OH, YES!

185
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:10,076
Smokey: HE DID IT.

186
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,912
HE HIT KARS WITH HIS HAMON.

187
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:14,114
( Kars groaning )

188
00:10:14,214 --> 00:10:15,448
JoJo: OFF YOU GO.

189
00:10:17,718 --> 00:10:20,053
( Kars groaning )

190
00:10:34,901 --> 00:10:37,237
I'LL GET YOU.

191
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:47,247
( men's boots shuffling )

192
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:49,983
Von Stroheim: OHH!
LOOK AT THAT.

193
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:52,786
KARS FELL RIGHT
ONTO HIS OWN CRYSTAL SPIKES.

194
00:10:52,819 --> 00:10:55,155
‐ ( men's chorus singing )
‐ ( Kars groaning )

195
00:10:57,057 --> 00:10:59,760
Von Stroheim: BWA HA HA HA!

196
00:10:59,826 --> 00:11:01,334
THE PILLAR MAN IS DONE!

197
00:11:01,434 --> 00:11:06,339
SEE?! THE HAMON WILL TRAVEL
RIGHT UP HIS ARM UND DO THE JOB!

198
00:11:06,439 --> 00:11:10,176
YOU'RE WEAK!
YOUR TIME ON EARTH IS UP!

199
00:11:10,276 --> 00:11:13,747
A MERE HUMAN
COULD FINISH YOU OFF NOW!

200
00:11:13,814 --> 00:11:15,782
( men yelling )

201
00:11:19,019 --> 00:11:20,687
♪

202
00:11:23,423 --> 00:11:25,592
( men gasp )

203
00:11:25,659 --> 00:11:27,594
( sizzling )

204
00:11:30,296 --> 00:11:34,134
Von Stroheim: OHH.
TRYING TO SPOOK US, EH?

205
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:37,838
NOW LET'S ELIMINATE HIM FOREVER.

206
00:11:37,871 --> 00:11:40,807
BRING OUT
THE ULTRAVIOLET AMPLIFIER.

207
00:11:40,874 --> 00:11:41,842
Germans: JAWOHL!

208
00:11:41,875 --> 00:11:44,477
( Lisa Lisa panting )

209
00:11:47,714 --> 00:11:49,215
JoJo: LISA LISA.

210
00:11:50,617 --> 00:11:52,452
( panting )

211
00:11:52,519 --> 00:11:56,189
KARS SAID THAT HE
WASN'T ACTUALLY PLANNING

212
00:11:56,222 --> 00:11:57,724
TO KILL YOU WITH HIS BLADE,

213
00:11:57,824 --> 00:12:01,401
SO I DON'T THINK
THAT YOUR WOUNDS ARE FATAL.

214
00:12:03,637 --> 00:12:06,740
WE NEED TO GET YOU
TAKEN CARE OF QUICKLY,

215
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:10,911
BUT I DON'T THINK THIS IS
THE DAY YOU'RE GOING TO DIE.

216
00:12:10,977 --> 00:12:12,178
♪

217
00:12:12,245 --> 00:12:13,313
( Smokey sighs )

218
00:12:13,379 --> 00:12:14,648
IT'S FINALLY DONE.

219
00:12:14,715 --> 00:12:17,884
Speedwagon: LOOKS LIKE IT,
AND I'M GLAD.

220
00:12:17,918 --> 00:12:19,920
Smokey: SAY, MR. SPEEDWAGON,

221
00:12:20,020 --> 00:12:21,087
‐ UM...
‐ Speedwagon: HUH?

222
00:12:21,187 --> 00:12:22,656
Smokey: CAN I PLEASE
ASK YOU SOMETHING?

223
00:12:22,723 --> 00:12:23,757
Speedwagon: OF COURSE.

224
00:12:23,857 --> 00:12:26,593
Smokey: WELL, WHY DID
GRANNY ERINA LIE TO JOJO?

225
00:12:26,693 --> 00:12:28,529
WHY'D SHE TELL HIM
THAT HIS MOTHER

226
00:12:28,595 --> 00:12:30,396
HAD DIED WHEN HE WAS LITTLE BOY?

227
00:12:30,430 --> 00:12:33,266
WHY DOES LISA LISA HIDE HER PAST

228
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:36,002
AND NOT TELL HIM
WHO SHE REALLY IS?

229
00:12:36,069 --> 00:12:37,571
Speedwagon: SMOKEY, THAT'S, UH‐‐

230
00:12:37,604 --> 00:12:41,041
Smokey: I KNOW GRANNY ERINA
TOLD ME NOT TO ASK YOU,

231
00:12:41,107 --> 00:12:42,943
BUT I'VE GOTTA FIGURE THIS OUT.

232
00:12:43,009 --> 00:12:44,745
I MEAN, SHE IS HIS MOTHER.

233
00:12:44,778 --> 00:12:47,213
KEEPING THAT INFORMATION
FROM HIM IS JUST AWFUL.

234
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:49,349
Speedwagon: SMOKEY.

235
00:12:50,283 --> 00:12:52,619
Smokey: JOJO AND GRANNY ERINA,

236
00:12:52,719 --> 00:12:53,620
THEY'RE MY FRIENDS.

237
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:56,389
BACK IN NEW YORK,
THEY BOTH SAVED ME.

238
00:12:56,456 --> 00:13:00,634
I WAS JUST A LOWLY PICKPOCKET,
BUT THEY HELPED ME OUT ANYWAY.

239
00:13:00,734 --> 00:13:02,402
THAT'S THE REASON I'M HERE.

240
00:13:02,468 --> 00:13:05,105
I'M GOING TO DO
ANYTHING I CAN TO HELP.

241
00:13:05,138 --> 00:13:08,274
♪

242
00:13:12,613 --> 00:13:15,949
( Speedwagon sighs )
ALL RIGHT THEN, SMOKEY.

243
00:13:15,982 --> 00:13:17,383
LET ME TELL YOU.

244
00:13:17,450 --> 00:13:20,821
IN NEW YORK, YOU PROVED
WHAT A GOOD FRIEND YOU WERE.

245
00:13:20,921 --> 00:13:24,124
YOU TOOK EXCELLENT CARE OF ERINA
WHILE I WAS GONE.

246
00:13:24,157 --> 00:13:28,261
BUT THIS, YOU CAN
NEVER REVEAL TO JOJO.

247
00:13:28,328 --> 00:13:31,932
THIS IS THE BUSINESS
OF THE JOESTAR FAMILY.

248
00:13:31,998 --> 00:13:35,669
FRIENDS OR NOT, WE DON'T HAVE
THE RIGHT TO TALK ABOUT IT.

249
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:45,078
THE NAME LISA LISA
IS MADE UP, AN ALIAS.

250
00:13:45,145 --> 00:13:48,749
HER REAL GIVEN NAME
IS ELIZABETH.

251
00:13:48,815 --> 00:13:49,683
RAISED AND TRAINED

252
00:13:49,783 --> 00:13:52,418
BY THE HAMON‐USER STRAIZO
YOU MET...

253
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:55,421
SHE AND ERINA'S SON,

254
00:13:55,488 --> 00:13:58,191
GEORGE JOESTAR, FELL IN LOVE.

255
00:13:58,291 --> 00:13:59,425
THEY GOT MARRIED.

256
00:14:03,036 --> 00:14:05,205
( baby JoJo crying )

257
00:14:06,973 --> 00:14:10,276
Speedwagon: SOON GEORGE
AND ELIZABETH HAD A SON.

258
00:14:10,343 --> 00:14:12,546
YOU KNOW HIM AS JOJO.

259
00:14:17,217 --> 00:14:19,820
JOJO'S FATHER, GEORGE, ENLISTED

260
00:14:19,886 --> 00:14:22,989
AS A MEMBER OF BRITAIN'S
ROYAL FLYING CORPS.

261
00:14:23,056 --> 00:14:27,661
AVIATION DEVELOPED RAPIDLY
DURING THE FIRST WORLD WAR,

262
00:14:27,728 --> 00:14:30,496
AND GEORGE WAS AMONG
THE BRAVE PILOTS

263
00:14:30,564 --> 00:14:32,966
TO FLY INTO BATTLE IN THE SKIES.

264
00:14:37,904 --> 00:14:39,472
HE STOOD OUT AS A HERO,

265
00:14:39,540 --> 00:14:42,543
EVEN AMONG THE MEMBERS
OF THE ROYAL FLYING CORPS.

266
00:14:43,409 --> 00:14:44,911
IT WAS THEN...

267
00:14:45,011 --> 00:14:46,647
♪

268
00:14:46,713 --> 00:14:49,082
THAT A GUT‐WRENCHING HORROR
FROM THE PAST

269
00:14:49,149 --> 00:14:52,318
CAME BACK TO HAUNT THE MEMBERS
OF THE JOESTAR FAMILY.

270
00:14:52,385 --> 00:14:54,420
50 YEARS EARLIER,

271
00:14:54,487 --> 00:14:58,224
DIO BRANDO CREATED
BLOODSUCKING ZOMBIES.

272
00:14:58,258 --> 00:15:00,594
STRAIZO, MYSELF, AND THE OTHERS

273
00:15:00,661 --> 00:15:03,369
BELIEVED THAT WE
HAD EXTERMINATED THEM.

274
00:15:03,436 --> 00:15:05,506
BUT ONE OF THEM HAD ESCAPED.

275
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:07,541
HE HID HIMSELF WITHIN SOCIETY

276
00:15:07,608 --> 00:15:10,611
AND LIVED FOR DECADES
UNDISCOVERED.

277
00:15:10,711 --> 00:15:14,881
HE WAS CUNNING, INTELLIGENT,
SUPREMELY DANGEROUS.

278
00:15:14,948 --> 00:15:17,684
( zombie growls )

279
00:15:17,751 --> 00:15:20,286
Speedwagon: HE CREATED NO SPAWN.

280
00:15:20,386 --> 00:15:23,389
HE DEVOURED THE BONES
AND HAIR OF HIS VICTIMS,

281
00:15:23,456 --> 00:15:26,259
LEAVING BEHIND
NO EVIDENCE OF HIS EXISTENCE.

282
00:15:26,292 --> 00:15:28,461
( bones crunching )

283
00:15:34,635 --> 00:15:36,603
Speedwagon:
AND BY SOME WRETCHED,

284
00:15:36,637 --> 00:15:38,772
WICKED TWIST OF FATE...

285
00:15:40,641 --> 00:15:42,776
HE HAD PLACED HIMSELF
IN POSITION

286
00:15:42,809 --> 00:15:45,646
AS A COMMANDER
IN THE ROYAL FLYING CORPS.

287
00:15:45,746 --> 00:15:48,982
Smokey: THE ROYAL FLYING CORPS?
WITH JOJO'S FATHER?

288
00:15:49,082 --> 00:15:50,551
Speedwagon: THE VERY SAME.

289
00:15:50,617 --> 00:15:54,655
GEORGE WAS OBSERVANT
AND FIGURED THIS OUT.

290
00:15:54,755 --> 00:15:57,924
HE HAD LISTENED WELL
TO STRAIZO AND MYSELF.

291
00:15:57,991 --> 00:16:01,668
BUT ULTIMATELY, GEORGE WAS
ONLY AN ORDINARY MAN.

292
00:16:01,768 --> 00:16:03,770
HE HAD CHARACTER AND TALENT,

293
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:08,241
BUT HE HAD NO TRAINING
IN THE WAYS OF HAMON.

294
00:16:08,308 --> 00:16:09,676
( George gasps )

295
00:16:09,743 --> 00:16:12,679
Speedwagon: BEFORE HE WAS ABLE
TO UNMASK THE COMMANDER,

296
00:16:12,746 --> 00:16:15,348
HE WAS DISCOVERED
BY HIS MONSTROUS QUARRY.

297
00:16:15,415 --> 00:16:19,319
HIS MESSAGE TO STRAIZO
WAS TOO LATE.

298
00:16:19,352 --> 00:16:22,288
( George gags )

299
00:16:22,355 --> 00:16:24,858
♪

300
00:16:24,958 --> 00:16:26,793
Speedwagon: GEORGE'S DEATH
WAS COVERED UP

301
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:30,030
AS AN UNFORTUNATE
NIGHTTIME PLANE CRASH.

302
00:16:32,198 --> 00:16:34,835
STRAIZO AND I
FOUND THIS SUSPICIOUS,

303
00:16:34,868 --> 00:16:39,005
SO WE INVESTIGATED AND
EVENTUALLY LEARNED THE TRUTH.

304
00:16:41,808 --> 00:16:45,311
THAT NIGHT,
ELIZABETH HELD AN INFANT JOJO

305
00:16:45,378 --> 00:16:48,549
AS I TOLD HER
WHAT WE HAD DISCOVERED.

306
00:16:51,618 --> 00:16:54,721
INSTEAD OF SHOWING GRIEF,

307
00:16:54,821 --> 00:16:58,625
SHE RAN OUT
INTENT ON BLOODY REVENGE.

308
00:17:03,870 --> 00:17:05,071
( zombie gasps )

309
00:17:07,407 --> 00:17:09,810
( screams )

310
00:17:09,876 --> 00:17:12,513
Speedwagon: SHE WAS
A GENIUS WITH HAMON,

311
00:17:12,579 --> 00:17:14,981
BUT SHE LET HER EMOTIONS
CONSUME HER.

312
00:17:16,182 --> 00:17:17,851
SHE WAS CARELESS.

313
00:17:17,918 --> 00:17:20,587
THERE WAS A WITNESS
TO THE COMMANDER'S DEATH.

314
00:17:20,654 --> 00:17:22,088
( soldier screams )

315
00:17:22,188 --> 00:17:24,090
( running footsteps )

316
00:17:24,190 --> 00:17:28,394
Speedwagon: THE MILITARY KNEW
NOTHING ABOUT ZOMBIES OR HAMON.

317
00:17:28,428 --> 00:17:31,598
THEY CONCLUDED
THAT FOR SOME UNKNOWN REASON,

318
00:17:31,698 --> 00:17:34,768
ELIZABETH HAD ATTACKED
THEIR BELOVED COMMANDER,

319
00:17:34,868 --> 00:17:38,705
KILLED HIM, THEN BURNED HIS BODY
TO HIDE THE CRIME.

320
00:17:38,772 --> 00:17:41,908
WORD SPREAD
AS ONLY BAD NEWS CAN,

321
00:17:41,942 --> 00:17:45,712
AND SOON SHE WAS KNOWN
AROUND THE WORLD AS A MURDERER

322
00:17:45,779 --> 00:17:48,582
AND TRAITOR TO THE WAR EFFORT.

323
00:17:48,615 --> 00:17:50,784
( running footsteps )

324
00:17:50,851 --> 00:17:52,786
♪

325
00:17:54,688 --> 00:17:56,122
( Lisa Lisa gasps )

326
00:18:03,704 --> 00:18:05,639
Speedwagon:
WE USED ALL THE RESOURCES

327
00:18:05,706 --> 00:18:09,375
OF THE SPEEDWAGON FOUNDATION
TO COVER HER TRAIL.

328
00:18:09,442 --> 00:18:11,712
ELIZABETH HAD TO LEAVE
ENGLAND BEHIND

329
00:18:11,778 --> 00:18:15,582
WITHOUT EVEN A WORD
OF GOODBYE TO HER SON.

330
00:18:15,649 --> 00:18:18,619
( JoJo crying )

331
00:18:18,652 --> 00:18:20,654
Speedwagon: ERINA KNEW
WHAT HAD OCCURRED,

332
00:18:20,721 --> 00:18:23,990
AND SHE GAVE ME
THIS SPECIFIC REQUEST.

333
00:18:24,057 --> 00:18:27,728
Erina: WHEN THE CHILD GROWS UP
AND ASKS ABOUT HIS PARENTS,

334
00:18:27,794 --> 00:18:31,665
PLEASE TELL HIM
THEY BOTH DIED IN THE WAR.

335
00:18:31,732 --> 00:18:34,067
( Speedwagon gasps )

336
00:18:34,134 --> 00:18:36,169
( sighs )

337
00:18:36,236 --> 00:18:39,139
Erina: THIS CHILD,

338
00:18:39,172 --> 00:18:41,274
POOR LITTLE CHILD.

339
00:18:43,844 --> 00:18:49,082
Speedwagon: AND SO IT WAS
THAT ELIZABETH BECAME LISA LISA.

340
00:18:55,121 --> 00:18:56,757
Smokey: WHY?

341
00:18:57,658 --> 00:18:59,359
WHY IS IT THAT WAY?

342
00:18:59,425 --> 00:19:02,769
AT LEAST LET HIM KNOW
HIS MOTHER'S NOT DEAD SOMEWHERE!

343
00:19:02,836 --> 00:19:05,539
Speedwagon: I KNOW
PAINFULLY WELL WHY.

344
00:19:05,639 --> 00:19:09,976
ERINA LOST HER HUSBAND
AND HER SON

345
00:19:10,043 --> 00:19:13,179
IN THE BATTLE BETWEEN HAMON
AND THE STONE MASKS.

346
00:19:13,213 --> 00:19:15,215
BUT THINKING OF HER GRANDSON,

347
00:19:15,281 --> 00:19:18,018
HER JOSEPH, HER JOJO,

348
00:19:18,051 --> 00:19:22,155
SHE DIDN'T WANT HAMON TO CREATE
YET ANOTHER HOLE IN HER LIFE!

349
00:19:22,222 --> 00:19:23,690
LISA LISA FEELS THE SAME.

350
00:19:23,724 --> 00:19:25,826
( Smokey gasps )

351
00:19:25,892 --> 00:19:27,828
♪

352
00:19:29,830 --> 00:19:33,499
WHAT TRAGEDY FOR THIS FAMILY.

353
00:19:33,567 --> 00:19:35,836
SUCH A MISERABLE FORTUNE.

354
00:19:37,571 --> 00:19:38,839
BUT NOW...

355
00:19:39,706 --> 00:19:41,575
IT'S BETTER.

356
00:19:43,143 --> 00:19:47,848
JOJO USED HAMON POSITIVELY
TO SAVE HIS MOTHER'S LIFE.

357
00:19:52,418 --> 00:19:54,154
MR. SPEEDWAGON.

358
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:55,221
Speedwagon: HMM?

359
00:19:55,255 --> 00:19:56,923
Smokey: THERE'S NO REASON
FOR LISA LISA

360
00:19:56,990 --> 00:19:59,225
TO HIDE THE TRUTH
FROM JOJO ANY LONGER.

361
00:19:59,259 --> 00:20:00,160
Speedwagon: EH?

362
00:20:00,226 --> 00:20:01,868
Smokey: HE ALREADY
KNOWS ABOUT HAMON,

363
00:20:01,935 --> 00:20:04,771
AND HE USED IT
TO SAVE HIS MOTHER'S LIFE.

364
00:20:04,838 --> 00:20:06,807
Speedwagon: THAT'S TRUE.

365
00:20:06,873 --> 00:20:10,176
BUT STILL IT'S NOT
MY DECISION TO MAKE.

366
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:14,347
IT'S A QUESTION OF HOW ERINA
AND LISA LISA FEEL.

367
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:15,949
Smokey: I GUESS.

368
00:20:16,016 --> 00:20:17,383
German: MAJOR!

369
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:19,185
WE'RE READY TO FIRE, SIR.

370
00:20:19,219 --> 00:20:22,889
Von Stroheim: EXCELLENT.
EVERYONE FOCUS ON HIM.

371
00:20:22,956 --> 00:20:26,359
UND NOW WE WILL SHARE
THE HONOR OF EXECUTING KARS.

372
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:27,561
Germans: JAWOHL!

373
00:20:28,529 --> 00:20:31,297
( men's chorus singing )

374
00:20:31,364 --> 00:20:35,702
( laughs ) NOW, KARS, DIE!

375
00:20:35,736 --> 00:20:38,672
I CAN'T BEGIN TO TELL YOU
HOW GOOD IT FEELS

376
00:20:38,739 --> 00:20:41,742
TO GIVE THIS ORDER MYSELF!

377
00:20:41,842 --> 00:20:43,977
( chorus continues )

378
00:20:58,725 --> 00:21:00,694
( all yell, gasp )

379
00:21:00,761 --> 00:21:02,769
Speedwagon: VON STROHEIM,
YOU MUST STOP!

380
00:21:02,869 --> 00:21:05,839
HE'S GOT THE RED STONE ATTACHED
RIGHT THERE ON HIS MASK!

381
00:21:05,906 --> 00:21:07,340
U.V. LIGHT WILL HELP HIM!

382
00:21:07,407 --> 00:21:09,042
Von Stroheim: NO, DAMN IT.

383
00:21:09,109 --> 00:21:10,010
STOP NOW!

384
00:21:10,076 --> 00:21:13,614
DON'T FIRE THE U. V. AMPLIFIER!

385
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:16,116
THIS CAN'T BE!

386
00:21:16,216 --> 00:21:18,118
( woman vocalizing )

387
00:21:18,218 --> 00:21:20,120
♪

388
00:21:35,468 --> 00:21:38,438
( Von Stroheim stammering )

389
00:21:38,471 --> 00:21:40,373
I DIDN'T SEE HIM WITH THE MASK.

390
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:43,644
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT HE HAD IT
ANYWHERE NEAR HIM.

391
00:21:43,710 --> 00:21:46,446
I DIDN'T SEE HIM
PUT IN THE RED STONE.

392
00:21:46,479 --> 00:21:48,214
Speedwagon: NO, IT CAN'T BE.

393
00:21:48,281 --> 00:21:49,415
DEAR GOD.

394
00:21:51,084 --> 00:21:52,218
JoJo: KARS.

395
00:21:52,285 --> 00:21:54,320
( woman vocalizing )

396
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:56,322
♪

397
00:22:08,241 --> 00:22:10,176
♪

398
00:22:17,150 --> 00:22:20,521
♪ I'LL BE THE ROUNDABOUT

399
00:22:20,621 --> 00:22:24,357
♪ THE WORDS
WILL MAKE YOU OUT AND OUT ♪

400
00:22:24,457 --> 00:22:29,696
♪ I SPEND THE DAY YOUR WAY

401
00:22:29,763 --> 00:22:31,998
♪ CALL IT MORNING
DRIVING THROUGH THE SOUND ♪

402
00:22:32,032 --> 00:22:35,869
♪ AND IN AND OUT THE VALLEY

403
00:22:35,969 --> 00:22:39,205
♪ IN AND AROUND THE LAKE

404
00:22:39,272 --> 00:22:41,542
♪ MOUNTAINS COME
OUT OF THE SKY ♪

405
00:22:41,642 --> 00:22:43,777
♪ AND THEY STAND THERE

406
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,481
♪ ONE MILE OVER,
WE'LL BE THERE ♪

407
00:22:48,549 --> 00:22:50,350
♪ AND WE'LL SEE YOU

408
00:22:52,986 --> 00:22:57,323
♪ 10 TRUE SUMMERS, WE'LL BE
THERE AND LAUGHING, TOO ♪

409
00:22:57,390 --> 00:22:59,059
♪ WITH YOU

410
00:22:59,159 --> 00:23:01,902
♪ 24 BEFORE, MY LOVE,
YOU'LL SEE ♪

411
00:23:02,002 --> 00:23:06,372
♪ I'LL BE THERE WITH YOU

412
00:23:06,406 --> 00:23:08,374
( vocalizing )

413
00:23:38,672 --> 00:23:40,406
♪

414
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,242
Von Stroheim:
HE HAS BECOME THE UBERMENSCH.

415
00:23:42,275 --> 00:23:44,678
Speedwagon: HE HAS COMPLETE
MASTERY OVER ORGANIC LIFE.

416
00:23:44,745 --> 00:23:47,047
Smokey: IS THERE REALLY NO WAY
TO STOP HIM, MR. SPEEDWAGON?

417
00:23:47,113 --> 00:23:49,249
Speedwagon:
KARS THE PILLAR MAN IS NO MORE.

418
00:23:49,282 --> 00:23:51,785
HE'S BECOME KARS,
THE ULTIMATE CREATION!

